then it's all right. so i guessed the problem is at set/get bookmark of IRow.

This is a user error (and a javadoc error, should be better documented). The bookmark is evaluated as an expression. In the ui, if you want to add the same bookmark you would write "row-bookmark" in the ui. Or something like:
if (...)
"row-bookmark";
else
"some-other-bookmark";

So what we are missing are the quotes. row.setBookmark( "row-bookmark" ) is evaluated as row-bookmark, not "row-bookmark". 
The correct way to set the bookmark would be:
row.setBookmark("\"row-bookmark\"");

I will add better javadoc and set this as fixed when the javadoc is updated.
